            <note xml:id="foot.f7"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1225.xml">Henrietta Darwin</ref> was at Moor Park, where she was undergoing hydropathic treatment. She returned to Down after ten weeks of therapy on 31 October 1857 (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f8">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2148.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, 30 September [1857]</ref>.</note>
